{
  "text": "The fluctuation dynamo has since been convincingly confirmed beyond the limits of Kazantsev's theory by numerical simulations of forced and flows [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , especially when R m ≥ Re. Such simulations are also able to follow the fluctuation dynamo into the non-linear regime where the Lorentz forces becomes strong enough to affect the flow as to saturate the growth of magnetic field.",
  "correct_citation": {
